      "text": "<b>Therefore</b>, consider playing games in the group. The games should emphasize achieving things together. Games that aim at distinguishing winners and losers are not suitable. The games should leave enough room for <i>[[PERSONAL COMMUNICATION]]</i>. Games improve group quality, and they are usually not very demanding, from an intellectual point of view, serving as a good way to relax. However, games can be dangerous if the participants do not like them or consider them childish or otherwise useless. Never use games if the participants do not want it.\n  ",
